⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Milon
node MSC · MSC · ⟦Milon:MSC:e02782⟧

WHO   — Milon — the bubble-blowing boy
WHAT  — The hero of Milon's Secret Castle — who climbs the labyrinthine Castle Garland, popping its every secret loose, to rescue Queen Eliza from the warlord Maharito.
WHERE — MSC · Milon's Secret Castle  Framework inputs: Milon's Secret Castle (Hudson Soft, NES 1988)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the queen is captive and the castle is stolen; because every blank wall may hide a way forward for the one stubborn enough to test it; because a boy with bubbles can take a castle back.
HOW   — By bubbles — blown at enemies to pop them, and at walls, blocks, and scenery to reveal hidden items, doors, money, and the crystals that unlock the way deeper in.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I have no sword and no spell — only bubbles, and a wall that surely hides a door.

